question: What is the population of Central Greece?
gold_query:
PREFIX geo: <http://www.opengis.net/ont/geosparql#>
PREFIX geof: <http://www.opengis.net/def/function/geosparql/>
PREFIX strdf: <http://strdf.di.uoa.gr/ontology#>
PREFIX uom: <http://www.opengis.net/def/uom/OGC/1.0/>
PREFIX owl: <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#>
PREFIX rdf: <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#>
PREFIX rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#>
PREFIX xsd: <http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#>
PREFIX yago: <http://yago-knowledge.org/resource/>
PREFIX y2geor: <http://kr.di.uoa.gr/yago2geo/resource/>
PREFIX y2geoo: <http://kr.di.uoa.gr/yago2geo/ontology/>
SELECT DISTINCT ?population WHERE { <http://yago-knowledge.org/resource/Central_Greece_(region)> y2geoo:hasGAG_Population ?population }
generated_query:
PREFIX geo: <http://www.opengis.net/ont/geosparql#>
PREFIX geof: <http://www.opengis.net/def/function/geosparql/>
PREFIX strdf: <http://strdf.di.uoa.gr/ontology#>
PREFIX uom: <http://www.opengis.net/def/uom/OGC/1.0/>
PREFIX owl: <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#>
PREFIX rdf: <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#>
PREFIX rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#>
PREFIX xsd: <http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#>
PREFIX yago: <http://yago-knowledge.org/resource/>
PREFIX y2geor: <http://kr.di.uoa.gr/yago2geo/resource/>
PREFIX y2geoo: <http://kr.di.uoa.gr/yago2geo/ontology/>
SELECT ?population WHERE {
  <http://kr.di.uoa.gr/yago2geo/resource/gadmentity_Central_Greece_GRC.8.1_1> ?p ?population .
  FILTER (datatype(?population) = <http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#integer> || datatype(?population) = <http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#decimal>)
}
LIMIT 1

PREFIX geof: <http://www.opengis.net/def/function/geosparql/>

PREFIX yago: <http://yago-knowledge.org/resource/>

PREFIX y2geoo: <http://kr.di.uoa.gr/yago2geo/ontology/>

PREFIX y2geoo: <http://kr.di.uoa.gr/yago2geo/ontology/>
SELECT (COUNT(DISTINCT ?village) AS ?count) WHERE { { SELECT DISTINCT ?village WHERE { ?village rdf:type y2geoo:OSM_village ; geo:hasGeometry ?vg . ?vg geo:asWKT ?vw . yago:Greece geo:hasGeometry ?geo . ?geo geo:asWKT ?geoWKT FILTER geof:sfWithin(?vw, ?geoWKT) ?lake rdf:type y2geoo:OSM_lake ; geo:hasGeometry ?lg . ?lg geo:asWKT ?lw FILTER geof:sfWithin(?vw, ?lw) } } UNION { SELECT DISTINCT ?village WHERE { ?village rdf:type y2geoo:OSM_village ; geo:hasGeometry ?vg . ?vg geo:asWKT ?vw . yago:Greece geo:hasGeometry ?geo . ?geo geo:asWKT ?geoWKT FILTER geof:sfWithin(?vw, ?geoWKT) ?forest rdf:type y2geoo:OSM_forest ; geo:hasGeometry ?fg . ?fg geo:asWKT ?fw FILTER geof:sfWithin(?vw, ?fw) } } }

SELECT (COUNT(DISTINCT ?village) AS ?count)
WHERE {
  ?village a <http://kr.di.uoa.gr/yago2geo/ontology/OSM_village> .

    <http://kr.di.uoa.gr/yago2geo/ontology/OSM_lake> <http://www.opengis.net/def/function/geosparql/sfContains> ?village .

}

PREFIX strdf: <http://strdf.di.uoa.gr/ontology#>
PREFIX uom: <http://www.opengis.net/def/uom/OGC/1.0/>
PREFIX owl: <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#>
PREFIX rdf: <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#>
PREFIX rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#>
PREFIX xsd: <http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#>
PREFIX yago: <http://yago-knowledge.org/resource/>
PREFIX y2geor: <http://kr.di.uoa.gr/yago2geo/resource/>
PREFIX y2geoo: <http://kr.di.uoa.gr/yago2geo/ontology/>
SELECT DISTINCT ?bay ?bayWKT WHERE {
  # Dublin geometry
  <http://yago-knowledge.org/resource/Dublin> geo:hasGeometry ?dublinGeo .
  ?dublinGeo geo:asWKT ?dublinWKT .
  
  # Parks in Dublin
  ?park rdf:type <http://kr.di.uoa.gr/yago2geo/ontology/OSM_park> .
  ?park geo:hasGeometry ?parkGeo .
  ?parkGeo geo:asWKT ?parkWKT .
  FILTER(geof:sfContains(?dublinWKT, ?parkWKT))
  
  # Bays
  ?bay rdf:type <http://kr.di.uoa.gr/yago2geo/ontology/OSM_bay> .
  ?bay geo:hasGeometry ?bayGeo .
  ?bayGeo geo:asWKT ?bayWKT .
  
  # Bay is east of park
  FILTER(strdf:right(?bayWKT, ?parkWKT))
}

  # The city of Cork

  ?county geo:hasGeometry ?countyGeo .
  ?countyGeo geo:asWKT ?countyWKT .

  ?corkCityGeo geo:asWKT ?corkCityWKT .
  
  FILTER(geof:sfTouches(?countyWKT, ?corkCityWKT))
  
  # Lakes contained in the county
  ?lake a <http://kr.di.uoa.gr/yago2geo/ontology/OSM_lake> .
  ?lake geo:hasGeometry ?lakeGeo .
  ?lakeGeo geo:asWKT ?lakeWKT .
  
  FILTER(geof:sfContains(?countyWKT, ?lakeWKT))
  
  # Get lake area
  ?lake <http://kr.di.uoa.gr/yago2geo/ontology/yago2geo/hasArea> ?lakeArea .
  
  # Subquery to find the maximum lake area among all lakes in bordering counties

      ?borderCounty a <http://kr.di.uoa.gr/yago2geo/ontology/OS_County> .
      ?borderCounty geo:hasGeometry ?borderCountyGeo .
      ?borderCountyGeo geo:asWKT ?borderCountyWKT .
      FILTER(geof:sfTouches(?borderCountyWKT, ?corkCityWKT))
      
      ?borderLake a <http://kr.di.uoa.gr/yago2geo/ontology/OSM_lake> .
      ?borderLake geo:hasGeometry ?borderLakeGeo .
      ?borderLakeGeo geo:asWKT ?borderLakeWKT .
      FILTER(geof:sfContains(?borderCountyWKT, ?borderLakeWKT))
      
      ?borderLake <http://kr.di.uoa.gr/yago2geo/ontology/yago2geo/hasArea> ?area .
    }
  }
  
  FILTER(?lakeArea = ?maxArea)
}

PREFIX owl: <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#>

}

PREFIX owl: <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#>
PREFIX rdf: <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#>
PREFIX rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#>
PREFIX xsd: <http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#>
PREFIX yago: <http://yago-knowledge.org/resource/>
PREFIX y2geor: <http://kr.di.uoa.gr/yago2geo/resource/>
PREFIX y2geoo: <http://kr.di.uoa.gr/yago2geo/ontology/>
ASK WHERE {
  # Regional units of Greece with population
  ?regionalUnit rdf:type <http://kr.di.uoa.gr/yago2geo/ontology/GAG_RegionalUnit> .
  
  # Assume regional units are spatially contained in Greece
  <http://yago-knowledge.org/resource/Greece> geo:hasGeometry ?greeceGeo .
  ?regionalUnit geo:hasGeometry ?ruGeo .
  ?regionalUnit <http://kr.di.uoa.gr/yago2geo/ontology/population> ?pop .
  
  # Filter regional units spatially contained in Greece
  FILTER(geof:sfWithin(?ruGeo, ?greeceGeo))
  
  # Beach contained in regional unit
  ?beach rdf:type <http://kr.di.uoa.gr/yago2geo/ontology/OSM_beach> .
  ?beach geo:hasGeometry ?beachGeo .
  
  # Beach contained in regional unit
  FILTER(geof:sfWithin(?beachGeo, ?ruGeo))
  
  # We want to restrict to top 5 least populated regional units
  {
    SELECT ?regionalUnit WHERE {
      ?regionalUnit rdf:type <http://kr.di.uoa.gr/yago2geo/ontology/GAG_RegionalUnit> .
      ?regionalUnit <http://kr.di.uoa.gr/yago2geo/ontology/population> ?pop .
      <http://yago-knowledge.org/resource/Greece> geo:hasGeometry ?greeceGeo .
      ?regionalUnit geo:hasGeometry ?ruGeo .
      FILTER(geof:sfWithin(?ruGeo, ?greeceGeo))
    }
    ORDER BY ASC(?pop)
    LIMIT 5
  }
}

question: Is the largest US State larger than England?

PREFIX geof: <http://www.opengis.net/def/function/geosparql/>
PREFIX strdf: <http://strdf.di.uoa.gr/ontology#>

PREFIX y2geor: <http://kr.di.uoa.gr/yago2geo/resource/>
PREFIX y2geoo: <http://kr.di.uoa.gr/yago2geo/ontology/>
ASK WHERE { { SELECT ?area WHERE { ?state rdf:type yago:wikicategory_States_of_the_United_States ; yago:hasArea ?area } ORDER BY DESC(?area) LIMIT 1 } yago:England yago:hasArea ?enarea FILTER ( ?area > ?enarea ) }

PREFIX geof: <http://www.opengis.net/def/function/geosparql/>
PREFIX strdf: <http://strdf.di.uoa.gr/ontology#>
PREFIX uom: <http://www.opengis.net/def/uom/OGC/1.0/>
PREFIX owl: <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#>
PREFIX rdf: <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#>
PREFIX rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#>
PREFIX xsd: <http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#>
PREFIX yago: <http://yago-knowledge.org/resource/>
PREFIX y2geor: <http://kr.di.uoa.gr/yago2geo/resource/>
PREFIX y2geoo: <http://kr.di.uoa.gr/yago2geo/ontology/>
ASK WHERE {
  # Get England's area
  <http://yago-knowledge.org/resource/England> <http://yago-knowledge.org/ontology/yago2geo/hasArea> ?englandArea .

  # Get areas of US states
  ?state <http://yago-knowledge.org/ontology/yago2geo/hasArea> ?stateArea .
  
  # Filter states to those that are part of the United States by URI pattern (heuristic)
  FILTER(CONTAINS(STR(?state), "United_States")) .

  # Find the maximum state area
  {
    SELECT (MAX(?stateArea) AS ?maxStateArea) WHERE {
      ?state <http://yago-knowledge.org/ontology/yago2geo/hasArea> ?stateArea .
      FILTER(CONTAINS(STR(?state), "United_States")) .
    }
  }

  # Compare max state area with England's area
  FILTER(?maxStateArea > ?englandArea)
}

question: Which city in England is adjacent to the most lakes?
gold_query:

PREFIX geof: <http://www.opengis.net/def/function/geosparql/>
PREFIX strdf: <http://strdf.di.uoa.gr/ontology#>

PREFIX y2geoo: <http://kr.di.uoa.gr/yago2geo/ontology/>
SELECT ?city WHERE { yago:England geo:hasGeometry ?eGeo . ?eGeo geo:asWKT ?eWKT . ?city rdf:type y2geoo:OSM_city ; geo:hasGeometry ?cGeo . ?cGeo geo:asWKT ?cWKT . ?lake rdf:type y2geoo:OSM_lake ; geo:hasGeometry ?lGeo . ?lGeo geo:asWKT ?lWKT FILTER ( geof:sfWithin(?cWKT, ?eWKT) && strdf:touches(?cWKT, ?lWKT) ) } GROUP BY ?city ORDER BY DESC(COUNT(?lake)) LIMIT 1
